fields.content:
#python3 code to print pyramid pattern using recursion
def pypart(n):
    if n==0:
        return
    else:
        pypart(n-1)
        print("* "*n)
  
# Driver Code
n = 5
pypart(n)

fields.title: Egg fried Recipe
fields.content:
Ingredients:

  • 2 cups cooked rice (preferably day-old rice)
  • 2-3 eggs
  • 1/2 cup mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, corn, etc.)
  • 2 tablespoons soy sauce
  • 1 tablespoon oil (vegetable or sesame oil)
  • 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
  • Salt and pepper to taste
  • Optional: chopped green onions for garnish

Instructions:

  1. Heat the oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
  2. Crack the eggs into a bowl and lightly beat them with a fork or whisk.
  3. Add the beaten eggs to the hot skillet and scramble them until they are fully cooked. Remove the scrambled eggs from the skillet and set them aside.
  4. In the same skillet, add the mixed vegetables and sauté them until they are tender. If using frozen vegetables, make sure to thaw them first.
  5. Add the cooked rice to the skillet with the vegetables and stir-fry for a few minutes until the rice is heated through and starts to slightly crisp.
  6. Sprinkle the garlic powder, salt, and pepper over the rice and vegetables. Mix well.
  7. Push the rice and vegetables to one side of the skillet and pour the soy sauce into the empty space. Allow it to heat for a few seconds.
  8. Add the scrambled eggs back to the skillet and mix everything together, coating the rice and vegetables with the soy sauce.
  9. Continue stirring and frying for a couple more minutes until everything is well combined and heated through.
  10. Taste and adjust the seasoning if needed.
  11. Remove from heat and garnish with chopped green onions if desired.
  12. Serve hot and enjoy your delicious egg fried rice!

Note: Feel free to customize this recipe by adding other ingredients like cooked chicken, shrimp, or additional vegetables to suit your taste preferences.
